1
00:01:12,520 --> 00:01:18,120
<i>[Meet Yourself]</i>

2
00:01:19,220 --> 00:01:22,720
<i>[Episode 22]</i>

3
00:01:50,900 --> 00:01:52,680
What are you thinking about?

4
00:01:54,340 --> 00:01:59,120
I'm thinking about how there are so many stars.

5
00:01:59,120 --> 00:02:00,880
They're dazzling.

6
00:02:02,420 --> 00:02:04,560
When I was young,

7
00:02:04,560 --> 00:02:09,820
my grandma would tell me stories during the summer.

8
00:02:09,820 --> 00:02:12,400
I'd be lying in the yard.

9
00:02:12,980 --> 00:02:15,520
My grandma had a fan in hand to keep me cool.

10
00:02:16,100 --> 00:02:20,440
She told me the legend of the Cowherd and Weaver Girl.

11
00:02:21,300 --> 00:02:27,580
She said that a new star appears in the sky after a person dies.

12
00:02:28,100 --> 00:02:32,820
I asked her which one was my grandpa.

13
00:02:32,820 --> 00:02:37,240
She said it was the one blinking at me.

14
00:02:40,500 --> 00:02:42,480
Your grandma is right.

15
00:02:42,480 --> 00:02:48,760
I think people return to the galaxy after their deaths.

16
00:02:48,760 --> 00:02:50,700
You believe in this too?

17
00:02:50,700 --> 00:02:52,500
I'm an atheist.

18
00:02:52,500 --> 00:02:55,160
I believe in science.

19
00:02:55,160 --> 00:02:59,960
I believe that nothing will truly disappear.

20
00:02:59,960 --> 00:03:03,280
Everything in this world has an energy of existence.

21
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:05,400
Energy doesn't vanish.

22
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:09,220
It can only be passed on endlessly.

23
00:03:09,220 --> 00:03:15,660
So, becoming a star after death has a scientific basis.

24
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:23,500
Can we become an animal, a cloud, or a plant?

25
00:03:25,300 --> 00:03:27,960
You'll become something you yearn to be.

26
00:03:28,580 --> 00:03:30,040
What do you want to become?

27
00:03:30,040 --> 00:03:32,180
My choice?

28
00:03:35,660 --> 00:03:37,260
I'd like to turn into the wind.

29
00:03:37,260 --> 00:03:38,920
The wind?

30
00:03:39,440 --> 00:03:44,060
When I miss someone, I can gently waft over to them.

31
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:46,080
They can sense me.

32
00:03:48,900 --> 00:03:52,220
If that's what you wish, you'll definitely turn into the wind.

33
00:03:52,220 --> 00:03:56,740
That's because energy is produced even in thought.

34
00:03:56,740 --> 00:03:58,240
That's magical!

35
00:03:58,240 --> 00:04:00,880
Don't probe. If you do, it'll become a scientific inquiry.

36
00:04:06,180 --> 00:04:08,000
What about you?

37
00:04:08,000 --> 00:04:10,160
What do you want to turn into?

38
00:04:15,740 --> 00:04:17,540
I'd like to turn into the rain.

39
00:04:20,420 --> 00:04:22,480
Why?

40
00:04:29,400 --> 00:04:34,920
But I believe Chen Nanxing will definitely turn into a star.

41
00:04:36,380 --> 00:04:40,280
When she was born, her dad noticed that it was about daybreak.

42
00:04:40,280 --> 00:04:44,320
The South Star was shining brightly in the distance.

43
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:47,040
So, he gave her the name Nanxing.

44
00:04:48,560 --> 00:04:50,900
The South Star?

45
00:04:50,900 --> 00:04:52,620
We're in the Northern Hemisphere.

46
00:04:52,620 --> 00:04:55,380
We can't see the South Star.

47
00:04:55,380 --> 00:04:58,240
When it's dawn, we might be able to see the Morning Star.

48
00:04:58,240 --> 00:05:00,120
That's in the east.

49
00:05:01,420 --> 00:05:03,240
We can't see the South Star?

50
00:05:03,240 --> 00:05:04,500
Nope.

51
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,880
Her dad probably got it wrong,

52
00:05:08,400 --> 00:05:09,640
but that's fine.

53
00:05:09,640 --> 00:05:11,840
She'd turn into a star anyway.

54
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:22,680
There are so many stars twinkling.

55
00:05:22,680 --> 00:05:27,520
I can't tell which one is my grandma, or grandpa, or Chen Nanxing.

56
00:05:28,180 --> 00:05:33,060
No matter which ones they are, they're looking at you.

57
00:05:39,060 --> 00:05:40,780
Can they see me?

58
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:43,380
Of course.

59
00:05:43,380 --> 00:05:47,900
They all hope that you are happy

60
00:05:47,900 --> 00:05:49,700
and living a good life.

61
00:05:52,840 --> 00:05:57,600
I always think so and assure myself,

62
00:06:04,900 --> 00:06:07,680
but I have too many regrets,

63
00:06:07,680 --> 00:06:09,300
too much I'm reluctant to let go of,

64
00:06:10,620 --> 00:06:12,080
too much remorse,

65
00:06:12,740 --> 00:06:15,100
and too many lingering attachments.

66
00:06:15,100 --> 00:06:20,920
Look. We had a lot of time,

67
00:06:22,020 --> 00:06:26,920
but we never traveled together.

68
00:06:29,420 --> 00:06:33,040
She must've been in pain for a long time,

69
00:06:37,300 --> 00:06:39,620
but I never expressed...

70
00:06:41,360 --> 00:06:45,480
any concern for her.

71
00:06:51,700 --> 00:06:54,180
I wasn't even by her side...

72
00:07:03,580 --> 00:07:07,700
when she was dying. She left this world alone.

73
00:07:11,940 --> 00:07:17,240
Each time I had fun with you guys, I'd feel upset the next second.

74
00:07:17,240 --> 00:07:21,480
I just wish you guys could also be friends with her.

75
00:07:21,480 --> 00:07:24,400
You guys would love her

76
00:07:24,400 --> 00:07:27,700
because she's a wonderful girl.

77
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:38,400
Well, tell me about her.

78
00:07:38,400 --> 00:07:40,420
What was she like?

79
00:07:47,820 --> 00:07:53,960
She was a very pure and bubbly person.

80
00:07:53,960 --> 00:07:58,400
Each time she was around, the weather didn't matter.

81
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:04,940
Be it sun, rain, snow, hail, or wind,

82
00:08:04,940 --> 00:08:07,500
you'd feel that it was a great day.

83
00:08:10,900 --> 00:08:16,760
Can there really be such a mystical person who makes every weather perfect?

84
00:08:19,220 --> 00:08:21,960
She was my wonder woman.

85
00:08:22,860 --> 00:08:24,720
I trust that.

86
00:08:25,500 --> 00:08:30,940
She's not here, and you're so depressed at the thought of her.

87
00:08:30,940 --> 00:08:34,760
However, you're delighted when you talk about her.

88
00:08:39,340 --> 00:08:41,560
That's true.

89
00:08:41,560 --> 00:08:43,120
Why?

90
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:48,960
That's because the utterance of her name brings her to life.

91
00:08:49,520 --> 00:08:52,220
When you stop talking about her,

92
00:08:52,220 --> 00:08:54,460
she'll truly vanish from this world.

93
00:08:58,500 --> 00:09:01,740
Unlike the countless strangers in this world,

94
00:09:02,260 --> 00:09:04,980
I might not be acquaintances with Chen Nanxing,

95
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:07,040
but she exists.

96
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:10,260
Those random strangers

97
00:09:10,260 --> 00:09:15,500
don't exist to me in a certain sense.

98
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:20,440
When you see me,

99
00:09:20,440 --> 00:09:22,780
talk to others about me

100
00:09:22,780 --> 00:09:25,060
and think about me, time and again,

101
00:09:25,860 --> 00:09:28,060
I'll be with you.

