162
00:14:05,100 --> 00:14:06,400
- Get going.
- Come on.

163
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,000
Let's go.

164
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,520
- Is this the only one?
- Yes, just this one.

165
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:11,400
- Okay.
- Off you go.

166
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:34,940
How is it?

167
00:14:34,940 --> 00:14:36,540
Does it taste good?

168
00:14:39,400 --> 00:14:41,520
It's a little weird.

169
00:14:42,100 --> 00:14:43,940
A strong seafood smell.

170
00:14:44,400 --> 00:14:47,500
That's because I added fish mint.

171
00:14:47,500 --> 00:14:49,440
Why did you add that?

172
00:14:49,440 --> 00:14:52,380
Don't you locals like the taste of it?

173
00:14:52,380 --> 00:14:54,980
We don't cook it this way.

174
00:15:01,780 --> 00:15:04,700
<i>[Damai: I boarded the plane. Don't worry.]</i>

175
00:15:04,700 --> 00:15:09,000
<i>[Have a safe trip. Let me know when you land.]</i>

176
00:15:13,980 --> 00:15:15,540
Why are you upset?

177
00:15:15,540 --> 00:15:17,800
Damai left.

178
00:15:21,120 --> 00:15:23,260
Isn't it time for you to leave?

179
00:15:24,020 --> 00:15:25,900
I'm not leaving.

180
00:15:26,600 --> 00:15:28,920
You have to leave sooner or later.

181
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:32,000
That's not right now.

182
00:15:33,820 --> 00:15:35,420
Next year?

183
00:15:37,300 --> 00:15:39,760
Next year is still miles away.

184
00:15:39,760 --> 00:15:42,920
I don't know, and I have no plans.

185
00:15:44,560 --> 00:15:46,980
It seems far away,

186
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:49,840
but time flies.

187
00:15:58,920 --> 00:16:00,820
What the heck is this taste?

188
00:16:00,820 --> 00:16:03,680
I shouldn't have added fish mint.

189
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:10,680
I didn't want to be blunt.

190
00:16:17,480 --> 00:16:19,380
Hongdou hasn't come over lately.

191
00:16:19,380 --> 00:16:21,400
What's she busy with?

192
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:23,180
A female tenant is leaving,

193
00:16:23,180 --> 00:16:26,060
so they've been having meals together.

194
00:16:27,100 --> 00:16:28,240
Has she left.

195
00:16:28,240 --> 00:16:29,720
Yes.

196
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:32,860
Well, invite her over for dinner tonight.

197
00:16:32,860 --> 00:16:35,680
I'll make scallion pancakes.

198
00:16:37,620 --> 00:16:40,440
Did you hear me?

199
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:42,660
Yes, I heard you.

200
00:16:56,260 --> 00:16:57,840
All done.

201
00:17:00,380 --> 00:17:02,120
It smells great.

202
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:05,760
Text A'Yao. Ask him when he'll be back for dinner.

203
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,140
Okay.

204
00:17:23,400 --> 00:17:26,140
Granny, he said Aunty Baoping wants him to stay for dinner.

205
00:17:26,140 --> 00:17:28,120
He asked us not to wait for him.

206
00:17:28,120 --> 00:17:30,280
Well, let's eat.

207
00:18:02,960 --> 00:18:06,120
Calm down. Take your time to explain.

208
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:09,060
<i>M-My dad is outrageous.</i>

209
00:18:09,060 --> 00:18:11,680
<i>I already promised to leave the house four days a week.</i>

210
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:13,760
<i>I even wrote a guarantee.</i>

211
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,460
<i>He said he had a present for me.</i>

212
00:18:16,460 --> 00:18:18,940
<i>I... I was pretty excited,</i>

213
00:18:18,940 --> 00:18:21,820
but it turned out like this!

214
00:18:23,180 --> 00:18:24,480
What's wrong with Damai?

215
00:18:24,480 --> 00:18:26,720
Her dad gave her a gift.

216
00:18:26,720 --> 00:18:28,260
<i>Hongdou, are you there?</i>

217
00:18:28,260 --> 00:18:29,300
Yes, I am.

218
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:30,780
I'm in the kitchen.

219
00:18:30,780 --> 00:18:34,300
Turn on your camera. Show us the gift from your dad.

220
00:18:34,300 --> 00:18:36,560
<i>Hold on.</i>

221
00:18:43,160 --> 00:18:44,820
It's so cute!

222
00:18:44,820 --> 00:18:47,420
Why are you peeing again?

223
00:18:47,420 --> 00:18:49,360
<i>I'll mop it later.</i>

224
00:18:51,160 --> 00:18:53,140
<i>How is it cute?</i>

225
00:18:53,140 --> 00:18:56,640
<i>My dad said I have to walk it four days a week.</i>

226
00:18:56,640 --> 00:18:57,960
<i>Four days!</i>

227
00:18:57,960 --> 00:19:01,940
<i>It can pee in the toilet on the days we don't walk.</i>

228
00:19:01,940 --> 00:19:06,020
<i>But dogs should have walks daily!</i>

229
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:09,800
I wouldn't have come back if I knew this would happen!

230
00:19:09,800 --> 00:19:11,420
Your dad is impressive.

231
00:19:11,420 --> 00:19:15,500
As expected of a teacher struggling with students daily.

232
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,780
Damai, I can really understand how you feel.

233
00:19:17,780 --> 00:19:20,020
Poor girl.

234
00:19:20,020 --> 00:19:21,460
I have to end the call.

235
00:19:21,460 --> 00:19:23,880
The floor needs to be mopped.

236
00:19:26,740 --> 00:19:29,160
You should finish that bowl of plain noodles quickly or they'll clump together.

237
00:19:29,160 --> 00:19:30,740
I can't guarantee its taste.

238
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:34,020
You've added lard oil. How can it taste bad?

239
00:19:42,800 --> 00:19:44,960
Has something been on your mind lately?

240
00:19:46,420 --> 00:19:47,900
No.

241
00:19:48,820 --> 00:19:50,660
Are you reluctant to leave?

242
00:19:51,500 --> 00:19:52,740
A little,

243
00:19:52,740 --> 00:19:56,180
but I can't keep spending my time so leisurely. Right?

244
00:19:56,180 --> 00:19:59,600
I have to return to an ordinary life and job.

245
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:01,540
What about you and Chairman Xie?

246
00:20:02,220 --> 00:20:04,480
What about us?

247
00:20:06,780 --> 00:20:11,280
You stargazed with him outside the tent when we went camping.

248
00:20:11,280 --> 00:20:13,360
I saw everything.

249
00:20:22,100 --> 00:20:25,160
<i>Xinxin, didn't you sleep well yesterday?</i>

250
00:20:25,160 --> 00:20:26,980
<i>I can chat with you on the road.</i>

251
00:20:26,980 --> 00:20:28,540
<i>Sure.</i>

252
00:20:28,540 --> 00:20:29,660
