Don't you want to progress further?

263
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,400
How can I do that?

264
00:20:54,400 --> 00:20:57,300
You can video call him.

265
00:20:57,300 --> 00:21:00,800
That's just keeping in touch.

266
00:21:00,800 --> 00:21:05,230
Our souls are only nourished

267
00:21:05,230 --> 00:21:10,100
through physical warmth and intimacy.

268
00:21:12,640 --> 00:21:15,960
In a new environment,

269
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:17,920
it's easy to lower your guard...

270
00:21:20,220 --> 00:21:23,480
once you start to relax.

271
00:21:25,020 --> 00:21:30,520
Someone can wander into your heart by accident.

272
00:21:32,780 --> 00:21:35,400
But I'm just a tourist.

273
00:21:36,820 --> 00:21:39,040
I don't belong here.

274
00:21:40,680 --> 00:21:42,520
He's already wandered in.

275
00:21:42,520 --> 00:21:44,660
What can you do?

276
00:21:46,060 --> 00:21:47,980
I don't know either.

277
00:21:47,980 --> 00:21:50,700
I've never been in such a situation before.

278
00:21:50,700 --> 00:21:52,780
I have no experience.

279
00:21:52,780 --> 00:21:55,720
So, I've been trying to avoid him lately.

280
00:21:58,580 --> 00:22:04,460
Hongdou, do you feel happier meeting him or avoiding him?

281
00:22:06,240 --> 00:22:08,180
I'm happy to see him.

282
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:11,100
Have you ever had a crush on someone in school?

283
00:22:11,100 --> 00:22:12,540
Yes.

284
00:22:12,540 --> 00:22:16,460
I had a high school classmate who excelled at his studies.

285
00:22:16,460 --> 00:22:19,800
We sat across the aisle from each other.

286
00:22:19,800 --> 00:22:22,000
Would the sight of him make your day?

287
00:22:22,000 --> 00:22:23,420
Even if he only said a word to you

288
00:22:23,420 --> 00:22:26,360
or touched your textbook briefly,

289
00:22:26,360 --> 00:22:29,600
you'd be over the moon.

290
00:22:29,600 --> 00:22:30,660
Yes.

291
00:22:30,660 --> 00:22:32,780
That's precisely it!

292
00:22:32,780 --> 00:22:34,960
Use your imagination.

293
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:37,400
What's the difference between then and now?

294
00:22:37,400 --> 00:22:39,340
You're happy to see him.

295
00:22:39,340 --> 00:22:41,800
Stay happy.

296
00:22:43,020 --> 00:22:45,860
Buddy, you have to leave someday.

297
00:22:45,860 --> 00:22:48,740
Every moment of happiness counts.

298
00:22:48,740 --> 00:22:51,460
Don't be hard on yourself or fight with your feelings.

299
00:22:51,460 --> 00:22:54,220
You're still on holiday anyway.

300
00:22:57,240 --> 00:22:59,100
That makes sense.

301
00:23:00,940 --> 00:23:02,780
I have more experience in love than you do.

302
00:23:02,780 --> 00:23:04,900
My words can be trusted.

303
00:23:18,340 --> 00:23:21,480
I want to be Monkey King! I want to be Monkey King!

304
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:23,780
You can only be Pigsy since you lost.

305
00:23:23,780 --> 00:23:26,500
I don't care! I want to be Monkey King!

306
00:23:26,500 --> 00:23:29,060
Guobao, can you be Monk Sha?

307
00:23:29,060 --> 00:23:33,240
No! I want to be Monkey King!

308
00:23:37,180 --> 00:23:38,580
How can you guys bully Guobao again?

309
00:23:38,580 --> 00:23:40,080
I asked you to get along.

310
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:43,280
No one bullied him. He wants to be Monkey King.

311
00:23:43,280 --> 00:23:45,220
Let him be that.

312
00:23:45,220 --> 00:23:46,600
I'm Monkey King.

313
00:23:47,500 --> 00:23:48,880
Aren't you Ultraman?

314
00:23:48,880 --> 00:23:50,200
Why are you Monkey King now?

315
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:53,620
Ultraman isn't in Journey to the West.

316
00:23:53,620 --> 00:23:54,940
Be quiet.

317
00:23:54,940 --> 00:23:56,740
Let's discuss this.

318
00:23:56,740 --> 00:24:01,340
Can we remove Pigsy from Journey to the West and let Ultraman join in?

319
00:24:01,340 --> 00:24:04,440
No, we can't. We have to take Pigsy with us.

320
00:24:04,440 --> 00:24:07,840
Ultraman has to fight monsters in the city.

321
00:24:07,840 --> 00:24:09,260
Okay, fine.

322
00:24:09,260 --> 00:24:11,980
Guobao! Guobao! Listen up!

323
00:24:11,980 --> 00:24:14,780
You're in kindergarten now. Does anyone else roll on the ground like you?

324
00:24:14,780 --> 00:24:16,540
- I want to be Monkey King!
- Fine!

325
00:24:16,540 --> 00:24:18,700
Jiabao is coming back this Sunday.

326
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:21,120
I'll let your sister pull you up.

327
00:24:24,260 --> 00:24:26,300
Aren't you going to keep rolling about?

328
00:24:26,860 --> 00:24:28,120
Come over here.

329
00:24:29,180 --> 00:24:31,560
I'll take you to wash your face.

330
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:33,040
You guys, listen up.

331
00:24:33,040 --> 00:24:35,720
You have to get along. Don't stir trouble.

332
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:38,340
If you're roleplaying Journey to the West,

333
00:24:38,340 --> 00:24:42,980
you have to take turns being Monk Tang, Monk Sha, Pigsy, and Monkey King. Got it?

334
00:24:42,980 --> 00:24:45,540
No way, I'm Monk Tang.

335
00:24:45,540 --> 00:24:47,820
Why are you bent on being a monk?

336
00:24:47,820 --> 00:24:50,500
Monk Tang has a noble dream. So do I.

337
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:52,400
So, I'm Monk Tang.

338
00:24:52,400 --> 00:24:53,400
Fine.

339
00:24:53,400 --> 00:24:57,720
Xiao Hu Lu, as long as you can add and subtract within ten,

340
00:24:57,720 --> 00:24:59,820
you can be a nun, a monk, or whatever you like.

341
00:24:59,820 --> 00:25:01,380
Okay?

342
00:25:01,980 --> 00:25:04,840
All right, let's wash your face.

343
00:25:04,840 --> 00:25:06,440
Goodness, Guobao.

344
00:25:06,440 --> 00:25:08,600
You're too old to be wailing in public.

345
00:25:08,600 --> 00:25:11,340
Aren't you embarrassed?

346
00:25:17,960 --> 00:25:20,900
A'Feng! I'm here.

347
00:25:21,880 --> 00:25:23,740
Where are they?

348
00:25:23,740 --> 00:25:25,940
They went out to eat.

349
00:25:27,260 --> 00:25:28,780
What are you eating?

350
00:25:28,780 --> 00:25:30,540
Vegetable dumplings.

351
00:25:32,060 --> 00:25:34,300
Brother A'Chang is already suffering from anemia. What are you doing?

352
00:25:34,300 --> 00:25:36,120
Do you also want to suffer from anemia?

353
00:25:36,120 --> 00:25:38,280
I added eggs in them.

354
00:25:38,280 --> 00:25:39,600
Eggs?

355
00:25:39,600 --> 00:25:41,440
How many will you even bear to add?

356
00:25:41,440 --> 00:25:43,520
I know you best.

357
00:25:43,520 --> 00:25:45,160
These only contain vegetables.

358
00:25:45,160 --> 00:25:47,520
Stop weaving this.

359
00:25:50,500 --> 00:25:52,480
I brought you good food.

360
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:54,260
What delicacies did Xiao Xi send you this time?

361
00:25:54,260 --> 00:25:57,240
These aren't from Xiao Xi. I made this myself.

362
00:25:59,820 --> 00:26:02,400
- Yellow beef ribs.
- Yellow beef?

363
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:05,540
Have a taste. Try one.

364
00:26:09,980 --> 00:26:11,420
Does it taste good?

365
00:26:11,420 --> 00:26:12,880
You're a marvelous cook.

366
00:26:12,880 --> 00:26:16,100
Finish everything. Eat up.

367
00:26:16,100 --> 00:26:18,960
Look at yourself.

368
00:26:18,960 --> 00:26:22,240
You need to eat more meat. Got it?

369
00:26:23,260 --> 00:26:24,920
When Xie Qiang is released

370
00:26:24,920 --> 00:26:28,880
and he sees both of you gaunt from illnesses,

371
00:26:28,880 --> 00:26:31,840
how would he feel? How would he feel?

372
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:35,680
Eat up. Finish everything!

373
00:26:35,680 --> 00:26:39,040
Got it? I'll eat the vegetable dumplings.

374
00:26:41,260 --> 00:26:43,080
How is it?

375
00:26:43,080 --> 00:26:44,860
Delicious.

376
00:26:46,060 --> 00:26:48,400
Grains are the best.

377
00:26:49,420 --> 00:26:50,540
I'm not eating that. I won't.

378
00:26:50,540 --> 00:26:52,640
Take one. No!

379
00:26:52,640 --> 00:26:54,240
You eat it.

380
00:26:54,780 --> 00:26:56,820
I can eat this. It's tasty.

381
00:27:08,840 --> 00:27:11,820
Okay, settle this payment first.

382
00:27:11,820 --> 00:27:13,300
Okay.

383
00:27:13,300 --> 00:27:17,980
Brother, Hongdou is about to leave our cafe.

384
00:27:17,980 --> 00:27:21,920
After some thought, I think it's best to recruit another worker.

385
00:27:21,920 --> 00:27:24,440
Didn't I ask you to do that ages ago?

386
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:27,740
I wasn't aware of these service problems.

387
00:27:27,740 --> 00:27:29,120
Hongdou has set new standards for us.

388
00:27:29,120 --> 00:27:31,380
We should keep them.

389
00:27:32,020 --> 00:27:34,500
Okay. You can take charge of it.

390
00:27:34,500 --> 00:27:36,440
I'll deal with it, then.

391
00:27:36,440 --> 00:27:39,000
Okay. I'm off.

392
00:27:39,960 --> 00:27:42,640
- Bye-bye.
- Bye.

393
00:27:56,900 --> 00:27:59,580
Uncle, is the foal doing well?

394
00:27:59,580 --> 00:28:01,180
Yes, it is.

395
00:28:02,020 --> 00:28:04,300
Here you go. I brought you some carrots.

396
00:28:04,300 --> 00:28:05,760
Okay.

397
00:28:39,900 --> 00:28:42,060
Why are you running so fast?

398
00:28:42,580 --> 00:28:44,420
I'm asking you a question!

399
00:28:48,500 --> 00:28:49,540
What are you doing?

400
00:28:49,540 --> 00:28:50,960
That's none of your business!

401
00:28:50,960 --> 00:28:53,680
Xiao Qin! You!

402
00:28:55,640 --> 00:28:57,160
Second Brother.

403
00:29:15,660 --> 00:29:17,220
What's wrong?

404
00:29:17,220 --> 00:29:19,320
Did you quarrel with your dad again?

405
00:29:20,540 --> 00:29:23,360
I thought he stopped forcing you to learn embroidery.

406
00:29:23,360 --> 00:29:25,940
He doesn't like Yang Zhinan.

407
00:29:25,940 --> 00:29:28,200
Who's Yang Zhinan?

408
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:29,960
A staff member of a homestay in the town.

409
00:29:29,960 --> 00:29:31,920
My boyfriend.

410
00:29:32,900 --> 00:29:35,200
You're in a relationship?

411
00:29:36,820 --> 00:29:38,780
Congratulations.

412
00:29:38,780 --> 00:29:40,760
Why doesn't your dad like him?

413
00:29:40,760 --> 00:29:43,860
He thinks the guy isn't dependable because he's much younger than me.

414
00:29:43,860 --> 00:29:45,040
How old is he?

415
00:29:45,040 --> 00:29:46,800
He's already 19 years old.

416
00:29:46,800 --> 00:29:48,760
Five years younger than you?

417
00:29:48,760 --> 00:29:50,920
So what?

418
00:29:50,920 --> 00:29:52,300
It's nothing.

419
00:29:52,300 --> 00:29:55,540
I just didn't know about this.

420
00:29:57,340 --> 00:29:59,520
Come over here. Let me tell you.

421
00:30:00,860 --> 00:30:02,240
He wooed me.

422
00:30:02,240 --> 00:30:05,920
He was a frequent customer at my place, but that raised my suspicions.

423
00:30:05,920 --> 00:30:08,800
They have a convenience store right in front of the homestay.

424
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:11,720
So, I asked him if he had a crush on me.

425
00:30:11,720 --> 00:30:13,920
He ran off in fright.

426
00:30:13,920 --> 00:30:17,200
The next day, he started to order takeouts for me.

427
00:30:19,620 --> 00:30:21,600
The takeouts aren't the reason.

428
00:30:21,600 --> 00:30:23,040
I'm not an easy catch.

429
00:30:23,040 --> 00:30:26,280
He had to woo me for a long time before I agreed.

430
00:30:27,180 --> 00:30:28,320
How long?

431
00:30:28,320 --> 00:30:30,740
More than a week.

432
00:30:31,820 --> 00:30:33,760
Actually, I wanted to start the relationship on the first day.

433
00:30:33,760 --> 00:30:37,060
Am I supposed to wait until the next Double Third Festival to sing him a love confession?

434
00:30:39,540 --> 00:30:41,000
Your dad is old.

435
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:42,640
It's hard for him to keep up with modern ideas.

436
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:44,540
Don't be mad at him.

437
00:30:44,540 --> 00:30:46,240
I'm not.

438
00:30:46,240 --> 00:30:48,800
He just doesn't seem pleased by anything I do.

439
00:30:48,800 --> 00:30:51,120
Today, we went to harvest scallions.

440
00:30:51,120 --> 00:30:53,700
He was worried about my mom, so he made my mom stay at home.

441
00:30:53,700 --> 00:30:55,220
I'm worried about him.

442
00:30:55,220 --> 00:30:57,500
So, I closed the store to go with him.

443
00:30:57,500 --> 00:31:01,160
He kept complaining that I'd only cause trouble.

444
00:31:01,160 --> 00:31:03,660
He even said I've been a sloth with no ambitions since young.

445
00:31:03,660 --> 00:31:05,640
Then, he started criticizing Yang Zhinan endlessly.

446
00:31:05,640 --> 00:31:08,040
That's why I flared up!

447
00:31:08,860 --> 00:31:12,000
You share your mom's temper.

448
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:13,020
Yes.

449
00:31:13,020 --> 00:31:14,580
He has to spare a thought for me.

450
00:31:14,580 --> 00:31:17,120
It's in my genes.

451
00:31:17,900 --> 00:31:20,480
But he said I was an imp.

452
00:31:20,480 --> 00:31:22,120
I never learned anything decent.

453
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:25,200
Even my boyfriend isn't any good.

454
00:31:25,200 --> 00:31:27,000
What's a good boyfriend?

455
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:30,040
Isn't someone I like a good boyfriend?

456
00:31:32,500 --> 00:31:34,000
You're right.

457
00:31:34,000 --> 00:31:35,260
Right?

458
00:31:35,260 --> 00:31:39,560
Uncle A'Yao, your words are always pleasant to the ears.

459
00:31:40,660 --> 00:31:43,620
Since you've finished chatting with me, get on with harvesting scallions.

460
00:31:43,620 --> 00:31:45,820
There's no rush. Let's chat.

461
00:31:45,820 --> 00:31:47,760
Tell me about how you're doing.

462
00:31:47,760 --> 00:31:52,500
Be frank with me. Are you dating Xu Hongdou from the courtyard?

463
00:31:52,500 --> 00:31:54,000
Not that again.

464
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:58,040
I told you, she's a tenant. Her lease will end next month.

465
00:31:58,040 --> 00:32:00,200
Is she really leaving?

466
00:32:00,200 --> 00:32:03,520
I thought you were pretty fond of her.

467
00:32:03,520 --> 00:32:05,000
I like her, too.

468
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:07,500
She's so fair.

469
00:32:09,360 --> 00:32:12,040
Uncle A'Yao, you're already so old.

470
00:32:12,040 --> 00:32:15,380
Girls won't want you if you don't take the initiative.

471
00:32:15,380 --> 00:32:17,440
Woo her. Make her stay.

472
00:32:17,440 --> 00:32:20,460
I bet you'll have to woo her for quite some time.

473
00:32:20,460 --> 00:32:21,820
Leave once you're done talking.

474
00:32:21,820 --> 00:32:24,940
Stop gabbing all that nonsense. You're just like your dad.

475
00:32:24,940 --> 00:32:27,420
Uncle A'Yao, how could you say that?

476
00:32:27,420 --> 00:32:29,040
How am I like my dad?

477
00:32:29,040 --> 00:32:30,920
I'm showing concern for you!

478
00:32:30,920 --> 00:32:32,100
I'm busy!

479
00:32:32,100 --> 00:32:34,560
Get on with your own task.

480
00:32:34,560 --> 00:32:37,580
Yang Zhinan is much better.

481
00:32:37,580 --> 00:32:40,560
Yang Zhinan is the best in this world.

482
00:33:04,500 --> 00:33:07,500
Hongdou likes eating chicken. Invite her over.

483
00:33:07,500 --> 00:33:10,680
Let's not. She probably ate her dinner by now.

484
00:33:10,680 --> 00:33:12,580
Try asking.

485
00:33:12,580 --> 00:33:13,920
I won't.

486
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:16,680
Ask her.

487
00:33:16,680 --> 00:33:19,400
I won't. You can do it if you want to.

488
00:33:21,260 --> 00:33:22,900
Hongdou!

489
00:33:22,900 --> 00:33:25,040
Don't shout!

490
00:33:25,040 --> 00:33:26,760
What's wrong with you?

491
00:33:26,760 --> 00:33:28,160
Well, what's wrong with you?

492
00:33:28,160 --> 00:33:30,040
Why are you pestering me to invite her over?

493
00:33:30,040 --> 00:33:31,820
She's leaving soon. Don't you know?

494
00:33:31,820 --> 00:33:33,240
I know.

495
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:36,900
That's why I want her to join us for more meals.

496
00:33:37,740 --> 00:33:39,200
I know what's on your mind.

497
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:40,920
Quash those thoughts.

498
00:33:40,920 --> 00:33:42,820
What's on my mind?

499
00:33:44,300 --> 00:33:47,500
Say it. What's on my mind?

500
00:33:48,500 --> 00:33:49,920
Say it!

501
00:33:49,920 --> 00:33:51,200
Granny!

502
00:33:51,200 --> 00:33:53,440
Xu Hongdou is a tourist.

503
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:55,440
You have to accept reality and give up on these fantasies.

504
00:33:55,440 --> 00:33:56,840
Stop inviting her over for meals all the time.

505
00:33:56,840 --> 00:33:58,480
She just feels bad to refuse.

506
00:33:58,480 --> 00:34:00,480
You've never invited the other tenants over.

507
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:02,420
That's not nice.

508
00:34:06,760 --> 00:34:08,620
Why are you staring at me?

509
00:34:08,620 --> 00:34:11,160
Invite Hongdou over for dinner.

510
00:34:12,100 --> 00:34:14,560
Do it yourself. I'm eating out.

511
00:34:15,700 --> 00:34:18,200
Where are you going this late?

512
00:34:18,200 --> 00:34:20,760
A'Yao, I won't invite her.

513
00:34:20,760 --> 00:34:23,600
I won't invite her, okay?

514
00:34:41,300 --> 00:34:42,600
Here you go. Your skewers are ready.

515
00:34:42,600 --> 00:34:43,420
- Okay.
- Thanks.

516
00:34:43,420 --> 00:34:44,960
You're welcome.

517
00:35:04,420 --> 00:35:05,940
What's wrong?

518
00:35:06,340 --> 00:35:08,660
You've been sitting here silently.

519
00:35:08,660 --> 00:35:10,500
What's wrong?

520
00:35:10,500 --> 00:35:11,780
You were busy.

521
00:35:11,780 --> 00:35:13,960
Who am I supposed to chat with?

522
00:35:14,820 --> 00:35:20,000
Tell me the truth. Did the deal with the bookstore fall through?

523
00:35:20,840 --> 00:35:23,280
Can't you be more positive about me?

524
00:35:23,280 --> 00:35:25,420
I want to be optimistic,

525
00:35:25,420 --> 00:35:28,600
but you're always sitting here with a can of beer.

526
00:35:28,600 --> 00:35:30,580
Your face will always be so gloomy.

527
00:35:30,580 --> 00:35:32,740
I bet a deal didn't go well.

528
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:41,360
I'm not fated to own a big company in this life.

529
00:35:42,220 --> 00:35:45,000
I can't bear the stress.

530
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:47,960
Every time I hear about your deals falling through,

531
00:35:47,960 --> 00:35:51,040
I feel like I'm on a roller coaster. It's just endless ups and downs.

532
00:35:51,040 --> 00:35:52,540
